  "rationale": "Jumping jacks primarily target the lower body, core, and shoulders, with only minimal involvement of the chest (pectorals) and insufficient mechanical tension or load to drive significant chest hypertrophy. Evidence-based hypertrophy exercises for the chest include presses, push-ups, cable flyes, and dips, which allow for progressive overload and greater chest muscle activation. No provided evidence supports jumping jacks as an effective method for increasing chest size.",
  "citations": [1, 2, 3]
